```csharp
using System;
using System.Runtime.InteropServices;

public static class NativeCompression
{
    [DllImport("compresslib", CallingConvention = CallingConvention.Cdecl, ExactSpelling = true)]
    public static extern int CompressBuffer(
        [In] byte[] input,
        UIntPtr inputLen,
        [Out] byte[] output,
        UIntPtr outputLen,
        out UIntPtr bytesWritten);
}
```

Key decisions:
- **`UIntPtr`** for `size_t` — matches pointer width (32-bit on x86).
- **`CallingConvention.Cdecl`** — standard for C APIs.
- **`[In]`/`[Out]`** attributes clarify marshalling direction for the byte arrays.
- Entry point matches the C name via `ExactSpelling = true`.
